      "bullets": [
        "Interviews reveal widespread Kubernetes over-engineering; many workloads are better suited for simpler setups like Docker Compose or AWS ECS.",
        "Candidates often struggle with core networking like CNIs and Ingress, focusing too much on basic YAML templating.",
        "There is a major knowledge gap between using managed services like EKS/GKE and understanding bare-metal control plane administration."
